cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel variant of the domain adversarial feature-learning framework, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and feature extraction, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with video surveillance, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
